 {\rm P}((Y-X)^2 \leq t) = {\rm P}(|Y-X| \leq \sqrt{t}) = H(\sqrt t ) - H( - \sqrt t ). 
 \frac{d}{{dt}}{\rm P}((Y - X)^2  \le t) = \frac{{h(\sqrt t )}}{{2\sqrt t }} + \frac{{h( - \sqrt t )}}{{2\sqrt t }} = \frac{{h(\sqrt t ) + h( - \sqrt t )}}{{2\sqrt t }}. 
